&lt;p data-start="161" data-end="291"&gt;The logo of &lt;span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"&gt;&lt;span class="whitespace-normal"&gt;Baskin-Robbins&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; contains a hidden design element that creates a sense of surprise for viewers. What is the hidden element in the logo, and how does it contribute to the brand’s identity?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start="398" data-end="506"&gt;Additionally, describe one idea for incorporating a similar “element of surprise” into your own logo design.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</mattext>
        </material>
        <response_str ident="response1" rcardinality="Single">
          <render_fib>
            <response_label ident="answer1" rshuffle="No"/>
          </render_fib>
        </response_str>
      </presentation>
